verses.text:
So
are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain;
which taketh away the life of the owners thereof.

If thou seekest her as silver, and searchest for her as
for
 hid treasures;

To deliver thee from the strange woman,
even from the stranger
which flattereth with her words;

Length of days
is in her right hand;
and in her left hand riches and honour.

Wisdom
is the principal thing;
therefore get wisdom: and with all thy getting get understanding.

Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth; and thy labours
be
 in the house of a stranger;

Riches and honour
are with me;
yea, durable riches and righteousness.

He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his own soul;
but
 he that despiseth his ways shall die.

Buy the truth, and sell
it not;
also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.

If thou forbear to deliver
them that are drawn unto death, and
those that are ready to be slain;
